mother brain deployment procedur using testgrid:

- motherbrain.ini: sample tesgrid manifest , create all the VM required (9 for motherbrain) using IS on playground .
ssh-copy-id -i on all the host, replace all the hostring in motherbrain.ini.

-install motherbrain package
sudo apt-get install motherbrain-deploy

- session.ini: description all the machine required in ordr to deply mother brain, each section shuld match the inventory file

tg -m demo/motherbrain/motherbrain.ini -l -s test --inventory  prod-hosts --session-manifest  demo/motherbrain/session.ini

test.py will be generated

ansible-playbook -i test.py  /usr/share/motherbrain-deploy/site.yml  -e mb_version=1.13.450c-1

more information regarding motherbrain:
https://confluence.arkena.net/display/SJTP/Ansible+commands

